"{\"uid\": \"essence.com-fashion-how-stella-jean-made-history-with-haitis-olympic-uniforms\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"When the general director of the Haitian Olympic Committee, Patrick Blanchet, commissioned fashion designerStella Jeanto create Haiti'sOlympic uniforms, the moment felt like a \\\"political call to arms without the hostility,\\\" she told ESSENCE.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haitian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Haitian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haitian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haitian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 60, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.9999725516033336, \"rank\": 2.0224888562210276e-05, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"score\": 0.589837395398953, \"rank\": 0.4226190476190751, \"text\": \"Blanchet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanchet_(harpsichord_makers)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the general director\", \"from\": 5, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"fashion designerStella\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 113}, {\"ngram\": \"Jeanto\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"Haiti'sOlympic uniforms\", \"from\": 128, \"to\": 151}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 163}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"political call\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 191}, {\"ngram\": \"arms\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 199}, {\"ngram\": \"the hostility\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"ESSENCE\", \"from\": 233, \"to\": 240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born to an Italian father and aHaitianmother, Jean's brilliance lies in her unique ability to translate her multicultural heritage into graphic garments that burst with untold stories.\", \"from\": 242, \"to\": 426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9648895898090369, \"rank\": 0.034317692708279245, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"aHaitianmother, Jean's brilliance\", \"from\": 272, \"to\": 305}, {\"ngram\": \"her unique ability\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 332}, {\"ngram\": \"her multicultural heritage\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 372}, {\"ngram\": \"graphic garments\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 394}, {\"ngram\": \"untold stories\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the designer, fashion functions as a cultural translator as well as \\\"a tool of counter-colonization,\\\" says Jean.\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 543, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the designer\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"a cultural translator\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"a tool\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"counter\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"colonization\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"Jean\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The designer envisioned outfitting the 2024 Summer Olympics team as an opportunity to change the common perception of Haiti as a \\\"troubled nation.\\\"\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999975613684632, \"rank\": 2.4386372771612347e-06, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The designer\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics team\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"the common perception\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"troubled nation\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since becoming the world's first free Black Republic in January 1804, after earning its independence from France, Haiti has suffered from civil unrest, gang violence, natural disasters, and extreme hardships.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"score\": 0.9998291000987817, \"rank\": 0.00016764373754231044, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999649709930812, \"rank\": 3.3672572050291955e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 807, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999975613684632, \"rank\": 2.4386372771612347e-06, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 756}, {\"ngram\": \"its independence\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"civil unrest\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"gang violence\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 858}, {\"ngram\": \"natural disasters\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme hardships\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 900}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These events loom large in the collective mind, but the arrival of the fashionable athletes at the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony may have wiped the slate clean.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These events\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"the collective mind\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the arrival\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"the fashionable athletes\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the slate\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jean's uniforms take a high-fashion approach to traditional sportswear, embracing unexpected silhouettes and bearing Haitian painter Philippe Dodard's \\\"Passage\\\" artwork.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1188, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9988807232631756, \"rank\": 0.0009464742808677411, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Dodard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Dodard\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jean's uniforms\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"a high-fashion approach\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional sportswear\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"unexpected silhouettes\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The inclusion of the artwork is particularly significant as it references the perilous journeys of Haitians across the Atlantic Ocean.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999980076828998, \"rank\": 1.992321247199508e-06, \"text\": \"Haitians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The inclusion\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"the artwork\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"the perilous journeys\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"the Atlantic Ocean\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The woman's style features a white sleeveless blazer with blue piping, crafted from recycled fabric and stamped with the HaitianOlympicemblem; a full skirt in primarily red and blue, boasting Dodard's painting; and a chambray button-down shirt, woven in Haiti from a \\\"blue cotton\\\" material native to the country.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1630, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999975613684632, \"rank\": 2.4386372771612347e-06, \"text\": \"Haiti\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The woman's style\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1393}, {\"ngram\": \"a white sleeveless blazer\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"blue piping\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1445}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled fabric\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"the HaitianOlympicemblem\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"a full skirt\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"Dodard's painting\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"a chambray button-down shirt\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"blue cotton\\\" material\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wasp-waisted, hip-padded silhouette of the blazer intentionally recalls Christian Dior's famous Bar jacket, Stella's way of subverting the dress codes French colonizers once imposed on enslaved Haitians.\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\", \"score\": 0.9993522735153222, \"rank\": 0.0006481463059963396, \"text\": \"Christian Dior\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dior\"}, {\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\", \"score\": 0.9990907924701588, \"rank\": 0.000910034940608707, \"text\": \"Stella\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.8267870637669742, \"rank\": 0.20950003294722142, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1888, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9999980076828998, \"rank\": 1.992321247199508e-06, \"text\": \"Haitians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wasp-waisted, hip-padded silhouette\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the blazer\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1743}, {\"ngram\": \"the dress codes\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To accessorize the look, a pair of white lace-up boots and one helix and lip piercing as nods to theTainos Indiansand their tradition of wearing jewelry on different body parts.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the look\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"a pair\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"white lace-up boots\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"one helix\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1966}, {\"ngram\": \"lip\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"nods\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"theTainos Indiansand\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"their tradition\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"jewelry\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"different body parts\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2074}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Taino Indians were the first people to inhabit Hasiti, according to the Library of Congress.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2080, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arawak\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2223379278454498e-34, \"text\": \"Taino\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arawak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arawak\"}, {\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_of_the_Americas\", \"score\": 0.9988227999651768, \"rank\": 0.0011785849340363653, \"text\": \"Indians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_of_the_Americas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indigenous_peoples_of_the_Americas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first people\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2115}, {\"ngram\": \"Hasiti\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"the Library\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"Congress\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equally powerful is the man's uniform, which also employs Dodard's artwork on the pants, and features a striped shirt layered under a light chambray jacket that nods to the Guayabera shirt, a traditional garment of Latin origin popular among Caribbean men.\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guayabera\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guayabera\"}, {\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 0.999811641119571, \"rank\": 0.00018830657650249273, \"text\": \"Latin\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}, {\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.5516971856314787e-12, \"text\": \"Caribbean\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caribbean\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the man's uniform\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2211}, {\"ngram\": \"Dodard's artwork\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2248}, {\"ngram\": \"the pants\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2261}, {\"ngram\": \"a striped shirt\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2291}, {\"ngram\": \"a light chambray jacket\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"a traditional garment\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The male model reminds us of the men we love in our society,\\\" says Haitian historian Berthrude Albert.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9988807232631756, \"rank\": 0.0009464742808677411, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}, {\"begin\": 2527, \"end\": 2533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 1.4694737515276396e-12, \"text\": \"Albert\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The male model\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2457}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2468}, {\"ngram\": \"our society\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our fathers, our uncles and grandfathers.\\\"\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Our fathers\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"our uncles\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"grandfathers\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another referential element of the male uniform is the patterned scarf, which young Stella grew up seeing both men and women wear with dignity at Haitian markets.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2663, \"end\": 2669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\", \"score\": 0.9990907924701588, \"rank\": 0.000910034940608707, \"text\": \"Stella\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_Price\"}, {\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"score\": 0.9988807232631756, \"rank\": 0.0009464742808677411, \"text\": \"Haitian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another referential element\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"the male uniform\", \"from\": 2610, \"to\": 2626}, {\"ngram\": \"the patterned scarf\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"both men\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2693}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2703}, {\"ngram\": \"dignity\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The uniforms are revolutionary in the way they weave different histories into compelli